rooms.Name: The quest preparation room
rooms.Description:
This room is one for people to wait in. All those who go through quests
must sit and meditate here while the final items in the quest are set
up. Perhaps you should look at the rules that are posted on a sign on
the wall.

ExtraDescs.Description:
Rules for this quest are as follows:

1. Groups can have a maximum of 75 levels and 4 players.
2. No multi's are allowed to participate.
3. If you level during the quest, it will not affect your group levels.
4. Groups may be formed.
5. If you die you may return to the quest.
6. You may not recall for supplies and return to the quest.
7. You may not obtain assistance from anyone not in your group.
8. The quest will continue until all the politicians are dead.
9. Stealing kills is not allowed, don't interfere in fights.
10. Don't piss off the IMMs running the quest or it might get cancelled.
Prizes will be awarded based on the group which wins.
Obtaining help from outside your group will result in disqualification. 
Once the quest has begun, there can be no additions/substitutions in the 
membership. Once you get a group together, the leader needs to tell 
MacLeod the members of his group. And the winning group will be 
determined by the number of kills made.

rooms.Description:
CONGRATS!!!!! You made it to the end of the quest!!!!!  If you were the first
one to get here, then you have one yourself a nice prize!!!!!!!!
Thank you for playing!

rooms.Name: At the Start of the Quest
rooms.Description:
Wait here calmly and prepare your self for the mental challenge ahead!  Do
not leave until you have been assigned a numbered direction to leave!
Leaving before I say so will get you removed from the quest.  The format
is simple, just go in the direction of what you think is the answer to the
question.  Many of them are hard, so do not get frustrated!

This is the first room of the quest.  You frantically look for a question, but
realize that this is the only the starting room.  This room can, hovever,
become as frustrating to see as that wonderful opeing menue on RoI if you
keep messing up!
